{"word":"ἐπανάγω","slug":"ἐπανάγω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπανάγω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-άξω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to bring up: to stir up, excite</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to draw back</i> an army, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to bring back</i> to the point, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to withdraw, retreat</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to put out to sea</i>, <el>ναῦς</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; and without <el>ναῦς</el>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>: so in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to put to sea against</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}